  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. The slope-intercept form of an equation for a line is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals, m x plus b\"></span>, where <span class=\"italic\">m</span> is the slope of the line and <span class=\"italic\">b</span> is the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-coordinate of the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-intercept of the line. It&rsquo;s given that the slope is 6, so <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"m equals 6\"></span>. It&rsquo;s also given that the line passes through the point <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"with coordinates 0 comma 8 \"></span> on the <span class=\"italic\">y</span>-axis, so <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"b equals 8 \"></span>. Substituting <span class=\"italic\"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"m equals 6 \"></span></span> and <span class=\"italic\"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"b equals 8 \"></span></span> into the equation <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals, m x plus b\"></span> gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals, 6 x plus 8\"></span>.<p>Choices B, C, and D are incorrect and may result from misinterpreting the slope-intercept form of an equation of a line.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
